Terms of Service for Brawl Bot

Welcome to Brawl Bot! By using this bot, you agree to the following terms and conditions. Please read them carefully.

Operation and Availability

Brawl Bot is a Discord bot that utilizes the Brawl Stars API to provide certain functionalities related to the Brawl Stars game.
The bot may be temporarily offline during server restarts or maintenance. We strive to minimize service interruptions, but they may occur occasionally.
Data Collection and Usage

Brawl Bot collects and stores only the Discord user ID and their Brawl Stars game ID.
This information is used solely to allow users to save their game IDs and retrieve them after a bot restart.
Discord IDs are stored only for the purpose of matching them with game information and are not used for any other purposes.
No data collected by Brawl Bot is sold, transmitted, or shared with third parties.
User Responsibilities

You are responsible for the accuracy of the information you provide to Brawl Bot.
You agree not to use Brawl Bot in a manner that violates Discord's terms of service, the Brawl Stars API terms, or any applicable laws.
Changes to the Terms

We reserve the right to modify these terms of service at any time. Changes will take effect immediately upon posting on right here.
It is your responsibility to regularly review the terms of service to stay informed of any changes.
Disabling Access

We reserve the right to disable your access to Brawl Bot if we determine, at our sole discretion, that you have violated these terms of service.
By using Brawl Bot, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to these terms of service. If you have any questions regarding these terms, please contact us at the discord server for the bot.
